parameters: \n<Guild Master>Katara...! What's the situation in town?
\n<Guild Master>Louie has disappeared!? At a time like this...!

\n<Guild Master>Something's wrong with Wanz!? Did the monsters do something
to her...?

\n<Guild Master>More importantly... I've figured out why the monsters
suddenly attacked. That bastard... set us up.

\n<Guild Master>This is a Howlstone. You know about it, right Katara? It was
certainly glowing yellow. But...

\n<Guild Master>This is a fake Howlstone. The Noblesse Count left it here.
Until a moment ago, it was definitely glowing yellow.

\n<Guild Master>It was emitting a blood-like red light... covered by a green
membrane of wind barrier, making it glow yellow.
\n<Grandpa>Could it be... a Blood Crystal!? Why is such a thing here!!

\n<Grandpa>It's a negative legacy from the ancient Attribute Wars. In
an era when people fought and killed each other. A crystal
of malice formed from blood and corpses...

\n<Guild Master>Monsters are masses of malice. With such a big piece, no
wonder they're gathering... it's their favorite treat.

\n<Guild Master>He had Radlo steal it on purpose. Do they hate us that
much...? Isn't looking down on us from above enough for
them?

\n<Guild Master>The light is getting stronger and stronger... just touching
it makes me feel like vomiting... that raccoon pushed this
crap onto us.

\n<Grandpa>Even if we give it to the monsters, they won't simply return
home. Rather, they might gain strength and destroy the town
even more.

\n<Guild Master>If only Lynx were here at a time like this. He was a barrier
master with the power of wind. If we could seal it again...
\n<Katara>The power of wind... I might be able to do it. I'll try!
!宝石ミニ幅狭
!宝石ミニ幅狭

\n<Katara>I did it... hah... hah... but this might not hold for very
long...

\n<Guild Master>No, you did well! If we move this thing somewhere now... the
monsters will be drawn to it.

\n<Grandpa>Surely not to the noble district!? If we do that, it will
only result in a large number of deaths again!

\n<Guild Master>Then what do you suggest we do? It's either the lower class
or the upper class that gets destroyed.

\n<Grandpa>...For now, let's have Katara, who can cast barriers, hold
onto it. By sealing its ominous power, the monsters should
become a bit more subdued.

\n<Guild Master>Tch... well, that's true. Let's reduce the number of
monsters while we can.
